        -- Posted by Raptor on 12:19 am on Dec. 11, 2001<p>
        asdf. gio, you are wrong ;) <br> <br>Max FLD: New document, whatever size you want, and a transparent background. Fill that layer with a dark shade of color - purple, blue, orange, whatever. but it has to be a dark shade.  <br> <br>Make a new layer, with a white circle. Guassian blur the hell out of it. Now click Edit -> Fill with mode behind, and color black. Change the layer blending mode to color dodge. Insta-glow. <br><img src="http://www.umich.edu/~jvhollan/images/fxzone/dodge.gif"> <br> <br>(Edited by Raptor at 11:21 am on Dec. 10, 2001)

